messages.message:
Hi all, please be aware DockerHub is reporting an active incident (https://www.dockerstatus.com/), and image pulls directly from DockerHub Registry  may timeout. If you see logs like the following in your CI jobs, this is the reason. :slightly_smiling_face:
```14:27:46  Error response from daemon: Head https://registry-1.docker.io/v2/library/node/manifests/latest: Get https://auth.docker.io/token?scope=repository%3Alibrary%2Fnode%3Apull&service=registry.docker.io: net/http: request canceled (Client.Timeout exceeded while awaiting headers)```
